{"title_page": "Sivakumar", "text_new": "{{other uses}}\n{{EngvarB|date=August 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2014}}\n{{Refimprove|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Sivakumar\n| image              = Sivakumar in 2016.jpg\n| caption            = Sivakumar in 2016\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1941|10|27}}<ref name=\"ibnlive1\">{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/sivakumar-not-hospitalised/303299-67.html|title=Sivakumar not hospitalised|date=1 November 2012|publisher=|accessdate=27 November 2016}}</ref>\n| nationality        = Indian\n| birth_place        = Madhampatty, [[Coimbatore District (Madras Presidency)|Coimbatore]], [[Madras Presidency]], [[British Raj|British India]] (now in [[Tamil Nadu]], [[India]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140903185612/http://cinema.maalaimalar.com/2014/08/25221939/Sivakumar-acted-in-193-films-i.html|title=Tamil Cinema news - Tamil Movies - Cinema seithigal|publisher=Maalaimalar|accessdate=27 November 2016}}</ref>\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| occupation         = Actor, Visual Artist\n| yearsactive        = 1965\u20132005\n| children           = [[Suriya]] <br>[[Karthi]]<br>Brindha\n| relatives          = {{unbulleted list|[[Jyothika]] (Daughter-in-law)|Ranjini Karthik (Daughter-in-law)\n}}\n| spouse             = Lakshmi (m.1974-present)\n| parents            = Rakkaiya <br>Palaniyammal\n}}\n\n'''Palaniswamy''', better known by his stage name '''Sivakumar''' (born 27 October 1941<ref name=\"ibnlive1\"/>) is an Indian film  actor and visual artist who has portrayed a wide range of leading and supporting roles onscreen in [[Tamil cinema]] and television. He made his acting debut in [[A. C. Trilogchander]]'s ''[[Kakkum Karangal (film)|Kakkum Karangal]]'' (1965).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140902070639/http://cinema.maalaimalar.com/2014/08/27221955/sivakumar-first-film-kakum-kar.html|title=Tamil Cinema news - Tamil Movies - Cinema seithigal|publisher=|accessdate=27 November 2016}}</ref> He has acted in over 190 movies in [[Tamil language|Tamil]]. He is also [[Ambidexterity|ambidextrous]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cinema.maalaimalar.com/2014/03/06231116/Cinema-history-7-years-drawing.html|title=Tamil Cinema news - Tamil Movies - Cinema seithigal|publisher=|accessdate=27 November 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"public\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/saying-it-with-sincerity/article1610080.ece|title=Saying it with sincerity|first=Malathi|last=Rangarajan|date=8 April 2011|publisher=|accessdate=27 November 2016|via=The Hindu}}</ref>\n\nHis sons [[Suriya]] and [[Karthi]] are actors as well as his elder daughter in-law [[Jyothika]]. And his daughter Brindha being a Playback Singer.\n\n==Career==\nSivakumar came into the industry in 1965 as a supporting actor. In the late 1960s as a lead hero, he starred in a few notable [[Tamil cinema|Tamil]] movies such as ''[[Kandan Karunai]]'', ''Thunivae Thozhan'' and ''Uyarndha Manidhan''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140904052005/http://cinema.maalaimalar.com/2014/08/28220446/ALS-Produced-by-kanthan-karuna.html|title=Tamil Cinema news - Tamil Movies - Cinema seithigal|publisher=|accessdate=27 November 2016}}</ref>  Between 1965 and 1974 he was predominantly playing supporting roles, in films with M.G. Ramachandran (2 films), Gemini Ganesan (7 films), Shivaji Ganesan (14 films) and R. Muthuraman (11 films) in the main lead roles. He has acted in supporting roles alongside Jayalalithaa in 7 films, which include ''Yarukkum Vetkam Illai'', ''Thirumangalyam'', ''Kavalkaran'', ''Shakti Leelai'', ''Ganga Gowri'', ''Motor Sundram Pillai'' and ''Annai Velankanni'' and was romantically paired opposite her in ''Kandan Karunai'' and ''Shri Krishna Leelai''. He started getting offers as the solo lead hero from 1974. Some of his successful films with him in lead role in the 1970s include ''Gumasthavin Magal'', ''Sollathaan Ninaikkiren'', ''Arangetram'', ''Vellikizhamai Viratham'', ''Panathukkaga'', ''Melnaattu Marumagal'', ''Pattikkaattu Raja'', ''Sindhudhe Vaanam'', ''Thangathile Vairam'', ''Bhadrakali, Aattukara Alamelu'', ''Bhuvana Oru Kelvi Kuri'', ''Kadavul Amaitha Medai'' and ''Enippadigal''. The director duo of Devaraj and Mohan directed Sivakumar in lead role in 9 films - ''[[Ponnukku Thanga Manasu]]'', ''Annakili'', ''Uravadum Nenjam'', ''Kavikkuyil'', ''Sainthadamma Sainthadu'', ''Chittu Kuruvi'', ''Rosaappo Ravikkai Kaari'', ''Poonthalir'' and ''Isai Paadum Thendral.'' In fact, Kamal Haasan and Rajinikanth have played supporting roles in films with Sivakumar in the lead role between 1972 and 1982.\n\nFrom 1973 to the early 1990s, Sivakumar was a leading actor in Kollywood, acting in successful movies such as ''[[Annakili]]'', ''[[Rosaappo Ravikkai Kaari]]'', ''[[Vandichakkaram]]'' and ''[[Sindhu Bhairavi (film)|Sindhu Bhairavi]]''.<ref name=\"hindu2\">{{cite news | last=| first= | title=   Sivakumar Educational Trust honours examination toppers    | date= 14 June 2009 | url =http://www.hindu.com/2009/06/14/stories/2009061457810200.htm| work =[[The Hindu]]| accessdate = 21 January 2010 | location=Chennai, India}}</ref><ref name=\"hindu3\">{{cite news |last=Ashok Kumar | first=S. R. |title=A chip off the old block?|date= 15 April 2003 |url=http://www.hinduonnet.com/mp/2003/04/15/stories/2003041500090200.htm |work =[[The Hindu]] |accessdate = 21 January 2010}}</ref> He has acted in nearly 200 films till date. He has co-starred with many leading Tamil actors of three generations, including [[Sivaji Ganesan]], [[M. G. Ramachandran]], [[Gemini Ganesan]], [[S.S. Rajendran]], [[R. Muthuraman]], [[A.V.M. Rajan]], [[Jaishankar]], [[Ravichandran (Tamil actor)|Ravichandran]], [[Kamal Haasan]], [[Rajinikanth]], [[Vijayakanth]], [[Sathyaraj]], [[Sarath Kumar]], [[Prabhu Ganesan]], [[Karthik Muthuraman]], [[Mohan (actor)|Mohan]], [[Arjun Sarja]], [[Ajith Kumar|Ajith]], [[Joseph Vijay|Vijay]], [[Vikram Kennedy|Vikram]] and [[Suriya Sivakumar]]. He is a two-time winner of [[Filmfare Awards South|Filmfare Awards]] for his performances in ''Rosaappo Ravikkai Kaari'' and ''Vandichakkaram''.  He is a two time recipient of [[Tamil Nadu State Film Awards]] for best actor in the films ''Avan Aval Adhu'' and ''Agni Sakshi''. His roles in ''[[Marupakkam]]'' and ''[[Sindhu Bhairavi (film)|Sindhu Bhairavi]]'' showed his versatility as an actor,<ref name=\"awards\">{{cite news| url=http://www.hindu.com/lf/2003/02/16/stories/2003021600450200.htm | location=Chennai, India | work=The Hindu | title=Bringing out the 'artist' in him | date=16 February 2003}}</ref> with the former winning the [[National Film Award for Best Feature Film|Golden Lotus Award for Best Feature Film]]. In the late 1990s, he ventured into [[Indian soap opera|television serials]] and is well known for his role as [[Raadhika]]'s husband in the famous TV serial ''[[Chithi (TV series)|Chithi]]''.\n\nIn recent times, he has ventured into public speaking, giving his opinion on various subjects, including [[Hindu]] theology. He has been praised for the fluency and style of his speeches.<ref name=\"public\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-15/actor-sivakumar-finishes-mahabharatham-in-just-2-hours-and-15-minutes.html|title=Actor Sivakumar finishes narrating Mahabharatham in just 2 hours and 15 minutes.|date=27 October 2015|publisher=|accessdate=27 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nSivakumar was born in Coimbatore. He is married to Lakshmi Kumari and the couple has three children; two sons who are actors, [[Suriya]] and [[Karthi]] and a daughter Brindha who is a playback singer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.google.com/search?kgmid=/m/0h73d9r&hl=en-IN&kgs=5d7345b8e1c191fe&q=Brindha+Sivakumar&shndl=0&source=sh/x/kp/osrp&entrypoint=sh/x/kp/osrp|title=Brindha Sivakumar - Google Search|website=www.google.com|access-date=2019-12-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140915103016/http://cinema.maalaimalar.com/2014/09/01231937/Sivakumar-wedding-preparations.html|title=Tamil Cinema news - Tamil Movies - Cinema seithigal|publisher=|accessdate=27 November 2016}}</ref> He is a devout [[Shaiva|Saiva]]-[[Shaktism|Saktha]] [[Hindu]] and a devotee of Lord [[Murugan|Sri Murugan]]. Sivakumar's elder daughter-in-law [[Jyothika Sadanah|Jyothika]] is a Kollywood actress.\n\n==Filmography==\n===1960s===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Film !!  Role !! Director !!  Co-stars !!  Notes\n|-\n| 1965\n| [[Kaakum Karangal]] || Surendar ||[[A. C. Tirulokchandar]] || [[S. S. Rajendran]], [[C. R. Vijayakumari]] || Debut Movie\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 1966\n| [[Motor Sundaram Pillai]] || ||[[S. Balasubramanian|Balu]] || [[Sivaji Ganesan]], [[Sowcar Janaki]], [[Ravichandran (Tamil actor)|Ravichandran]], [[Kanchana (actress)|Kanchana]], [[Jayalalithaa]] ||\n|-\n| [[Thaaye Unakkaga]] || ||[[P. Pullaiah]] || [[Sivaji Ganesan]], [[Padmini (actress)|Padmini]], [[S. S. Rajendran]], [[C. R. Vijayakumari]], [[Jayalalithaa]], [[R. Muthuraman]] ||\n|-\n| [[Saraswati Sabatham]] || [[Vishnu|Lord Vishnu]] ||[[A. P. Nagarajan]] || [[Sivaji Ganesan]], [[Gemini Ganesan]], [[Savitri (actress)|Savitri]], [[Padmini (actress)|Padmini]], [[K. R. Vijaya]], [[Devika]] ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 1967\n| [[Kandhan Karunai]] || [[Muruga|Lord Murugan]] ||[[A. P. Nagarajan]] || [[Sivaji Ganesan]], [[Gemini Ganesan]], [[Savitri (actress)|Savitri]], [[K. R. Vijaya]], [[Jayalalithaa]] ||\n|-1982\n| [[Kaavalkaaran]] || Chandran ||[[P. Neelakantan]] || [[M. G. Ramachandran]], [[Jayalalithaa]] ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" | 1968\n| [[Panama Pasama]] || ||[[K. S. Gopalakrishnan]] || [[Gemini Ganesan]], [[B. Saroja Devi]] ||\n|-\n| [[Thirumal Perumai]] || [[Vishnu|Lord Vishnu]] ||[[A. P. Nagarajan]] || [[Sivaji Ganesan]], [[Padmini (actress)|Padmini]], [[K. R. Vijaya]], [[Sowcar Janaki]] ||\n|-\n| Paal Manam || ||[[K. S.