{"title_page": "La Hiedra", "text_new": "{{short description|Mexican professional wrestler}}\n{{Infobox professional wrestler\n|name        = La Hiedra\n|names       = '''La Hiedra'''\n|image       = La hiedra by ric capullo colored by danolvera dc0nivb-pre.jpg\n|image_size  = \n|caption     = \n|height      = {{height|m=1.73}}<!-- In Mexico they measure height in meters so that should be first -->\n|weight      = {{convert|80|kg|lb|abbr=on}}<!--In Mexico they measure weight in kilograms so that should be first -->\n|birthname   = \n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1997|05|18}}\n|birth_place = [[Nuevo Laredo]], [[Tamaulipas]]\n|death_date  = \n|death_place = \n|resides     = \n|billed      = \n|parents     = [[Sangre Chicana]] (father)\n|relatives   = {{Unbulleted list|Sangre Chicana Jr.  (brother)|Sangre Imperial  (brother)|Hijo de Sangre Chicana (brother)|Lady Chicana  (sister)|[[Lluvia]] (sister)|[[\u00c1guila Solitaria]] (uncle)|[[Herodes (wrestler)|Herodes]] (uncle)|\u00c1guila Solitaria Jr. (cousin)|[[Herodes Jr.]] (cousin)}}\n|trainer     = Kendor Jr.<br>[[Laredo Kid]]<br>[[Sangre Chicana]]<br>[[Villano IV]]\n|debut       = {{dts|2010|11|14}}\n|retired     = \n|website     = \n}}\n'''La Hiedra''' (born May 18, 1997) is a Mexican ''[[lucha libre|luchadora]] enmascarada'', or [[wrestling mask|masked]] [[professional wrestler]] currently signed to [[Lucha Libre AAA Worldwide]] (AAA). La Hiedra's real name is not a matter of public record, as is often the case with masked wrestlers in Mexico where their private lives are kept a secret from the wrestling fans.<ref name=Mondo>{{cite book | author= Madigan, Dan | title= Mondo Lucha Libre: the bizarre & honorable world of wild Mexican wrestling | publisher= HarperColins Publisher | year= 2007 | chapter = Okay... what is Lucha Libre? | pages = 29\u201340 | isbn=978-0-06-085583-3}}</ref> La Hiedra is a second generation wrestler, the daughter of [[Sangre Chicana]].\n\n==Professional wrestling career==\n===Independent circuit (2011-2014)===\nLa Hiedra was originally trained by her father, Sangre Chicana before making her professional wrestling debut on November 14, 2010. La Hiedra made his debut on the independent circuit where defeated Amazona, La Hechicera and Rey Tornado. On September 16, 2011 in '' LLF Remembrance '', La Hiedra was defeated before Lady Puma in an individual single. On October 2, 2011, La Hiedra along with La Bandida was defeated before Princess Maya.\n\nOn November 6, 2011, La Hiedra made her debut in ''Promociones Cantu'' as part of [[Lucha Libre AAA Worldwide|AAA]] where she teamed with [[Mari Apache]] and Street Boy where they defeated Black Mamba, Lady Puma and La Hechicera.\n\n===Lucha Libre AAA Worldwide (2015\u2013present)===\nOn June 1, 2015, La Hiedra made her debut for [[Lucha Libre AAA Worldwide|AAA]], one of Mexico's largest wrestling promotions. In her first AAA match she teamed up with [[El Hijo de Pirata Morgan]], La Parka Negra and [[Taya Valkyrie]], defeated to El Elegido, [[Faby Apache]], Perseus & [[Pimpinela Escarlata]]. La Hiedra, along with [[Lady Shani]], [[Goya Kong]] and [[Lady Maravilla]] were all unsuccessful in their efforts to win the Reina de Reinas championship from [[Taya Valkyrie]] at the [[H\u00e9roes Inmortales IX]] show, La Hiedra's first championship match in AAA.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.f4wonline.com/mexico/aaa-heroes-inmortales-ippv-results-104-alberto-el-patron-vs-johnny-mundo-rey-mysterio-antonio | title=AAA Heroes Inmortales iPPV results (10/4): Alberto el Patron vs. Johnny Mundo, Rey Mysterio, Antonio Pena tribute match | last=Bihari | first=Robert | date=October 5, 2015 | accessdate=October 5, 2015 | work=[[Wrestling Observer Newsletter]]}}</ref> On November 6, 2015, she teamed up with Mamba, losing to Goya Kong and Pimpinela Escarlata. On March 19, 2017, La Hiedra competed in a fight to be to #1 Contender for the [[AAA Reina de Reinas Championship]], losing to [[Ayako Hamada]].<ref name=SLRdR2017>{{cite web|url=http://superluchas.com/2017/03/20/aaa-resultados-rey-de-reyes-2017-19032017-johnny-mundo-triple-monarca-argenis-gana-la-espada-y-ayako-hamada-es-la-nueva-reina/|title=AAA: Resultados \u201cRey de Reyes 2017\u201d \u2013 19/03/2017 \u2013 Johnny Mundo triple monarca; Argenis gana la espada y Ayako Hamada es la nueva reina|author=Dark Angelita|date=March 20, 2017|accessdate=March 20, 2017|work=Superluchas|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\nOn August 26 at ''[[Tripleman\u00eda XXVI]]'', La Hiedra teamed up with [[Angelikal]] for the [[AAA World Mixed Tag Team Championship]] against [[El Hijo del Vikingo]] and [[Vanilla Vargas|Vanilla]], Dinast\u00eda and [[Lady Maravilla]] and Ni\u00f1o Hamburguesa and Big Mami, where they managed to retain their titles.<ref name=OvacionexXXVI>{{cite web | url=https://ovaciones.com/triplemania-xxvi-cayo-la-mascara-del-hijo-del-fantasma-y-la-cabellera-de-faby-apache/ | title=Tripleman\u00eda XXVI: Cay\u00f3 la m\u00e1scara del Hijo del Fantasma y la cabellera de Faby Apache | date=August 26, 2018 | accessdate=August 26, 2018 | work=Ovaciones | language=Spanish | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180827075254/https://ovaciones.com/triplemania-xxvi-cayo-la-mascara-del-hijo-del-fantasma-y-la-cabellera-de-faby-apache/ | archive-date=August 27, 2018 | url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nLa Hiedra is the daughter of professional wrestler [[Sangre Chicana|Andr\u00e9s Dur\u00e1n Reyes]], better known under the [[ring name]] Sangre Chicana (\"Chicano Blood\"),<ref name=WWE>{{cite web | url=https://superluchas.com/siete-luchadoras-mexicanas-que-wwe-deberia-considerar-para-su-elenco/ | title=Siete luchadoras mexicanas que WWE deber\u00eda considerar para su elenco | trans-title=Seven Mexican wrestlers that WWE should consider for its roster | first=Carlos | last=Acosta | language=Spanish | date=May 18, 2016 | accessdate=March 6, 2019 | work=[[S\u00faper Luchas]]}}</ref> the sister of Sangre Chicana Jr. and half sister of [[Lluvia]].<ref name=WWE/> unlike her father or her brother La Hiedra decided to work as a ''[[Face (professional wrestling)|tecnico]]'' while her father was one of the most famous rulebreakers (also known as a ''[[Heel (professional wrestling)|rudo]]'') of the 1980s. She is the niece of wrestler Herodes and the cousin of wrestler [[Herodes Jr.]]<ref name=MondoFamily>{{cite book|author=Madigan, Dan|title=Mondo Lucha a Go Go: the bizarre & honorable world of wild Mexican wrestling|publisher=HarperColins Publisher|year=2007|chapter=A family affair|pages=128\u2013132|isbn=978-0-06-085583-3}}</ref>\n\n==Championships and accomplishments==\n* '''[[DDT Pro-Wrestling]]'''\n** [[Ironman Heavymetalweight Championship]] ([[Ironman Heavymetalweight Championship#Title history|1 time]])\n*'''Promociones EMW'''\n**EMW World Women's Championship (1 time, current)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Lucha Libre AAA Worldwide roster}}\n{{Los Mercenarios}}\n{{Portal bar|Biography|Mexico}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hiedra, La}}\n[[Category:1997 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Mexican female professional wrestlers]]\n[[Category:Masked wrestlers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Mexican professional wrestler}}\n{{Infobox professional wrestler\n|name=La Hiedra\n|names='''La Hiedra'''\n|image= [[File:La hiedra by ric capullo colored by danolvera dc0nivb-pre.jpg|thumb|dibujo de  la luchadora la hiedra de triple a]]\n|image_size=\n|caption=\n|height={{height|m=1.73}}<!-- In Mexico they measure height in meters so that should be first -->\n|weight={{convert|80|kg|lb|abbr=on}}<!--In Mexico they measure weight in kilograms so that should be first -->\n|birthname=\n|birth_date={{birth date and age|1997|05|18}}\n|birth_place=[[Nuevo Laredo]], [[Tamaulipas]]\n|death_date=\n|death_place=\n|resides=\n|billed=\n|parents=[[Sangre Chicana]] (father)\n|relatives={{Unbulleted list|Sangre Chicana Jr.  (brother)|Sangre Imperial  (brother)|Hijo de Sangre Chicana (brother)|Lady Chicana  (sister)|[[Lluvia]] (sister)|[[\u00c1guila Solitaria]] (uncle)|[[Herodes (wrestler)|Herodes]] (uncle)|\u00c1guila Solitaria Jr. (cousin)|[[Herodes Jr.]] (cousin)}}\n|trainer=Kendor Jr.<br>[[Laredo Kid]]<br>[[Sangre Chicana]]<br>[[Villano IV]]\n|debut={{dts|2010|11|14}}\n|retired=\n|website=\n}}\n'''La Hiedra''' (born May 18, 1997) is a Mexican ''[[lucha libre|luchadora]] enmascarada'', or [[wrestling mask|masked]] [[professional wrestler]] currently signed to [[Lucha Libre AAA Worldwide]] (AAA). La Hiedra's real name is not a matter of public record, as is often the case with masked wrestlers in Mexico where their private lives are kept a secret from the wrestling fans.<ref name=Mondo>{{cite book | author= Madigan, Dan | title= Mondo Lucha Libre: the bizarre & honorable world of wild Mexican wrestling | publisher= HarperColins Publisher | year= 2007 | chapter = Okay... what is Lucha Libre? | pages = 29\u201340 | isbn=978-0-06-085583-3}}</ref> La Hiedra is a second generation wrestler, the daughter of [[Sangre Chicana]].\n\n==Professional wrestling career==\n===Independent circuit (2011-2014)===\nLa Hiedra was originally trained by her father, Sangre Chicana before making her professional wrestling debut on November 14, 2010. La Hiedra made his debut on the independent circuit where defeated Amazona, La Hechicera and Rey Tornado. On September 16, 2011 in '' LLF Remembrance '', La Hiedra was defeated before Lady Puma in an individual single. On October 2, 2011, La Hiedra along with La Bandida was defeated before Princess Maya.\n\nOn November 6, 2011, La Hiedra made her debut in ''Promociones Cantu'' as part of [[Lucha Libre AAA Worldwide|AAA]] where she teamed with [[Mari Apache]] and Street Boy where they defeated Black Mamba, Lady Puma and La Hechicera.\n\n===Lucha Libre AAA Worldwide (2015\u2013present)===\nOn June 1, 2015, La Hiedra made her debut for [[Lucha Libre AAA Worldwide|AAA]], one of Mexico's largest wrestling promotions. In her first AAA match she teamed up with [[El Hijo de Pirata Morgan]], La Parka Negra and [[Taya Valkyrie]], defeated to El Elegido, [[Faby Apache]], Perseus & [[Pimpinela Escarlata]]. La Hiedra, along with [[Lady Shani]], [[Goya Kong]] and [[Lady Maravilla]] were all unsuccessful in their efforts to win the Reina de Reinas championship from [[Taya Valkyrie]] at the [[H\u00e9roes Inmortales IX]] show, La Hiedra's first championship match in AAA.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.f4wonline.com/mexico/aaa-heroes-inmortales-ippv-results-104-alberto-el-patron-vs-johnny-mundo-rey-mysterio-antonio | title=AAA Heroes Inmortales iPPV results (10/4): Alberto el Patron vs. Johnny Mundo, Rey Mysterio, Antonio Pena tribute match | last=Bihari | first=Robert | date=October 5, 2015 | accessdate=October 5, 2015 | work=[[Wrestling Observer Newsletter]]}}</ref> On November 6, 2015, she teamed up with Mamba, losing to Goya Kong and Pimpinela Escarlata. On March 19, 2017, La Hiedra competed in a fight to be to #1 Contender for the [[AAA Reina de Reinas Championship]], losing to [[Ayako Hamada]].<ref name=SLRdR2017>{{cite web|url=http://superluchas.com/2017/03/20/aaa-resultados-rey-de-reyes-2017-19032017-johnny-mundo-triple-monarca-argenis-gana-la-espada-y-ayako-hamada-es-la-nueva-reina/|title=AAA: Resultados \u201cRey de Reyes 2017\u201d \u2013 19/03/2017 \u2013 Johnny Mundo triple monarca; Argenis gana la espada y Ayako Hamada es la nueva reina|author=Dark Angelita|date=March 20, 2017|accessdate=March 20, 2017|work=Superluchas|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\nOn August 26 at ''[[Tripleman\u00eda XXVI]]'', La Hiedra teamed up with [[Angelikal]] for the [[AAA World Mixed Tag Team Championship]] against [[El Hijo del Vikingo]] and [[Vanilla Vargas|Vanilla]], Dinast\u00eda and [[Lady Maravilla]] and Ni\u00f1o Hamburguesa and Big Mami, where they managed to retain their titles.<ref name=OvacionexXXVI>{{cite web | url=https://ovaciones.com/triplemania-xxvi-cayo-la-mascara-del-hijo-del-fantasma-y-la-cabellera-de-faby-apache/ | title=Tripleman\u00eda XXVI: Cay\u00f3 la m\u00e1scara del Hijo del Fantasma y la cabellera de Faby Apache | date=August 26, 2018 | accessdate=August 26, 2018 | work=Ovaciones | language=Spanish | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180827075254/https://ovaciones.com/triplemania-xxvi-cayo-la-mascara-del-hijo-del-fantasma-y-la-cabellera-de-faby-apache/ | archive-date=August 27, 2018 | url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nLa Hiedra is the daughter of professional wrestler [[Sangre Chicana|Andr\u00e9s Dur\u00e1n Reyes]], better known under the [[ring name]] Sangre Chicana (\"Chicano Blood\"),<ref name=WWE>{{cite web | url=https://superluchas.com/siete-luchadoras-mexicanas-que-wwe-deberia-considerar-para-su-elenco/ | title=Siete luchadoras mexicanas que WWE deber\u00eda considerar para su elenco | trans-title=Seven Mexican wrestlers that WWE should consider for its roster | first=Carlos | last=Acosta | language=Spanish | date=May 18, 2016 | accessdate=March 6, 2019 | work=[[S\u00faper Luchas]]}}</ref> the sister of Sangre Chicana Jr. and half sister of [[Lluvia]].<ref name=WWE/> unlike her father or her brother La Hiedra decided to work as a ''[[Face (professional wrestling)|tecnico]]'' while her father was one of the most famous rulebreakers (also known as a ''[[Heel (professional wrestling)|rudo]]'') of the 1980s. She is the niece of wrestler Herodes and the cousin of wrestler [[Herodes Jr.]]<ref name=MondoFamily>{{cite book|author=Madigan, Dan|title=Mondo Lucha a Go Go: the bizarre & honorable world of wild Mexican wrestling|publisher=HarperColins Publisher|year=2007|chapter=A family affair|pages=128\u2013132|isbn=978-0-06-085583-3}}</ref>\n\n==Championships and accomplishments==\n* '''[[DDT Pro-Wrestling]]'''\n** [[Ironman Heavymetalweight Championship]] ([[Ironman Heavymetalweight Championship#Title history|1 time]])\n*'''Promociones EMW'''\n**EMW World Women's Championship (1 time, current)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Lucha Libre AAA Worldwide roster}}\n{